cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the segmentation and analysis of 3-D image stacks, which is a common topic in computer vision research (cs.CV). The focus is on the analysis of biological resistance of plant tissue to fungal infection, which involves quantifying features such as fungal penetration depth and branching of the fungal network, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) or multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the use of a synthetic hyphal network generator and a minimum spanning tree method, which could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) or neural networks (cs.NE).
